Program: Discovery
Title: Astronaut special
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrx6l
Last Broadcast Date: 04 September 1998
In a Discovery special, an interview with Charlie Duke. It's been over a quarter of a century since man stepped foot on the moon, the programme speaks to astronaut Charlie Duke who flew on Apollo 16. He explains how he became a fighter pilot and how he eventually ended up being one of the first men to go to the moon. Show less